===Etymology===
From Middle English '''[[percynne]]''' < Middle French '''[[persien]]''' < Latin '''*[[Persianus]]''' < Latin '''[[Persia]]''' < Greek '''[[Περσίς]]''' < Old Persian '''[[Pārsa]]'''.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)ʒən|-ɜː(r)ʒən]]

===Proper noun===
'''Persian''' (''plural:'' [[Persians]])

#A person from [[Persia]] ([[Iran]]).
#A group of very similar languages spoken primarily in Iran, Afghanistan, and Tajikistan, Persian belongs to the Southwestern branch of the [[Iranian]] subfamily of the Indo-Iranian family of languages. Indo-Iranian itself is a subfamily of the Indo-European language family. Closely related languages include [[Kurdish]], [[Pashto]], and [[Avestan]].
#A [[pastry]] local to the Thunder Bay region often compared to either a [[cinnamon]] [[bun]] or a [[donut]] topped with [[pink]] [[icing]]. (local [[colloquialism]], ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thunder_Bay%2C_Ontario Thunder Bay, Ontario], [[Canada]]'')
#A breed of [[cat]].

====Usage====
*Persian is the name applied to the official language of [[Iran]]. This language is also spoken in [[Tajikistan]] and some parts of [[Afghanistan]]. 
*The name "Farsi" (the local name for Persian) has developed currency in English to refer to the dialect spoken in Iran. Afghans usually call it [[Dari]], and the version spoken in Tajikistan is called Tajiki Persian or simply Tajiki.

